        <odd id="aspace_3688f70fe181278a87504f4176c70449">
          <head>General note</head>
          <p>Text with item: "This so-called 'Journal' of Luther Rice, 1819-26, was actually more of an account book for financial activities relating to the college. Rice was a slovenly bookkeeper and his disorganization led to severe monetary problems. He was blamed for the financial crisis of the college in 1826 and a move was made to investigate his operations. Their report was that Rice was clear of any immoral conduct but was a 'very loose accountant...with very imperfect talents for the disboursement of the money.'"</p>
        </odd>
